properties.headline: COVID-19 Border Control - TIBOOBURRA Fortville Gate Road at Queensland border
properties.otherAdvice:
The Queensland Government has implemented enhanced border control measures, including border passes and identification screening.

Any person that has been in a declared COVID-19 hotspot during the past 14 days must not enter Queensland. All of Victoria and Greater Sydney are currently declared COVID-19 hotspots. From 1am Saturday 8 August, all local government areas in NSW and ACT will also be declared COVID-19 hotspots.

Anyone attempting to enter Queensland from NSW must complete a Queensland Border Declaration Pass.

  • This border control point is accessible via a coded lock.
  • Declaration pass holders must call Thargomindah Police Station on 07 4655 3200 between 8am and 5pm for the code to gate.
  • Pass holders should call in advance due to a lack of suitable reception at the border control point.

properties.headline: CHANGED TRAFFIC CONDITIONS The Northern Road stage 4 - LUDDENHAM The Northern Road between Mersey Road AND Eaton Road
properties.otherAdvice:
As of 3pm Friday 11th September 2020 all temporary long term lane closures and temporary long term speed reductions will be reinstated to the ultimate configuration.  

Northern Road between Mersey Road and Adams Road traffic will now be driving onto the ultimate northbound and ultimate southbound carriageway, four lanes/two way·        

Traffic out of Dwyer Road onto The Northern Road will only be allowed to turn left-in and left-out with a U-turn bays have been provided at traffic lights to the north and south of Dwyer Road.

properties.headline: HAZARD Road damage - WOMBEYAN CAVES Wombeyan Caves Rd between Langs Rd AND Goodmans Ford
properties.otherAdvice:

properties.headline: CHANGED TRAFFIC CONDITIONS The Northern Road stage 5 - ORCHARD HILLS The Northern Road between Glenmore Parkway AND Eaton Road
properties.otherAdvice:

  • Installation and commissioning of temporary traffic signals at the intersection of The Northern Road and Defence Establishment Orchard Hills (DEOH) Access Road.
  • Switch traffic from the existing The Northern Road alignment onto the new northbound carriageway past the DEOH Access Road.
  • Opening of the new U-turn bay opposite the DEOH Access Road permitting access for traffic from the south only.
  • Three way stop slow arrangement at DEOH Access Road intersection at night to perform the traffic switching.
  • The existing shoulder widths on the southbound will be maintained and will remain compliant to the requirements of cyclists. On the northbound cyclists will be directed onto the newly constructed off road shared path.
  • Closure of the southbound overtaking lane past the Bradley Street intersection to facilitate future traffic switch onto the new southbound carriageway, to occur on 25 September 2020

properties.headline: CHANGED TRAFFIC CONDITIONS - NEW ACCESS ROAD OPENING - ROZELLE Victoria Road to Anzac Bridge
properties.otherAdvice:
From 7am Saturday 26 September 2020, drivers travelling south on Victoria Rd towards the city will use a new temporary 3-laned road called the Anzac Bridge Access Road to join the Anzac Bridge.

The entry point to the new access road is from the left lanes on Victoria Rd and is 130 metres earlier than the existing left turn on approach to The Crescent intersection.

Drivers will join the Anzac Bridge from the left hand lanes and will need to merge into the right lanes for access to the City.

Motorists should exercise caution, check directional signage and be aware of the new changed traffic conditions in the area.

This new road will be in place for approximately 2 years while the intersection is being upgraded.
